Package server.feldobjects

package server.feldobjects
  • Class Summary
    Class
    Description
    Antenna
    The FeldObject PriorityAntenna: The priority antenna helps determine whose turn it is.
    CheckPoint
    The FeldObject Checkpoint: You must reach checkpoints in numerical order.
    ConveyorBelt
    The FeldObject Conveyor belt: conveyor belts move any robot resting on them one or two spaces in the direction of the arrows.
    Empty
    The FeldObject Empty: PlaceHolder without any Function
    EnergySpace
    The FeldObject Energy space: When you end a register on an energy space, if there is an energy cube there, take it.
    FeldObject
    The type Feld object.
    Gear
    The FeldObject Gear: Gears rotate robots resting on them 90 degrees in the direction of the arrows.
    Laser
    The FeldObject Board laser: Board Lasers fire, hitting any robots in their line of sight.
    Pit
    The FeldObject Pit: If you land on a pit, you immediately fall in and must reboot your robot.
    PushPanel
    The FeldObject Push panel: Push panels push any robot resting on them into the next space in the direction the push panel faces.
    RestartPoint
    The FeldObject Restart point: When you fall off the board or into a pit, or when you activate a worm card, you must reboot your robot.
    RobotLaser
    The FeldObject Robot laser: Robot lasers fire in the direction a robot is facing.
    StartPoint
    The FeldObject Start point: Where you place your robots initially.
    Wall
    The FeldObject Wall: Robots cannot move through walls, and robot and board lasers cannot shoot through walls.
